    "created_at": "2013-08-06T22:00:06Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-08-06T22:02:50Z",
    "body": "Why bother having `unsafe` at all, if we're not guaranteeing other functions are memory safe? Memory safety has to be black or white, or Rust is no better than C++. A thread overrunning the stack and clobbering memory of other threads is a big deal.\n\nAn alternative is to _forbid_ functions using more than N stack space, and reserve N space as guard pages. If you don't have virtual memory you need `__morestack` to provide memory safety though.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
