    "updated_at": "2013-08-08T16:39:16Z",
    "body": "The conclusion was that we would always use split stacks, but on 64-bit platforms with overcommit we would make the initial segment large enough that it doesn't need to grow in typical use. This was also already implemented in the old runtime.\n\nFor freestanding Rust the question is more open - certainly one can build without split stacks if they like.\n",
